    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix null pointer dereference in decode_SIB1 function\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_SIB1()` function in the LTE RRC UE module was vulnerable to null pointer dereference and array out-of-bounds access when processing malformed or incomplete SIB1 messages. This issue could cause the UE to crash during initial cell selection, particularly when connecting to cells with incomplete configuration.\n\nThe root cause was missing validation of pointer and array bounds before accessing nested data structures in the decoded SIB1 message. The function assumed all optional fields were present and properly formatted.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c`: Added comprehensive null pointer checks and bounds validation in `decode_SIB1()` function\n- Added validation for PLMN identity list array access\n- Added validation for MCC/MNC digit array access\n- Added validation for scheduling info list array access\n- Added validation for SIB mapping info array access\n- Added fallback values for critical parameters when data is missing\n\n"
}